The motion passes, but not without significant strain on the <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> coalition! The liberal parties have managed to override conservative resistance, but this has created visible cracks in the bourgeois fortress. The [? if not kvp_formed and dnvp_ideology == "Moderate": <span style="color: #3E88B3;">DNVP</span>?][? if kvp_formed: <span style="color: #0087DC;">KVP</span>?] agrarian wing is particularly displeased with this leftward shift.

[? if bruning_austerity_limited == 1: We have successfully prevented Brüning from implementing planned tax cuts for high earners, maintaining progressive taxation. ?][? if bruning_austerity_limited == 2: We have successfully pressured the Bürgerblock into restoring the 40-hour workweek, though wage improvements remain limited. ?][? if bruning_austerity_limited >= 3: We have successfully forced the reversal of some civil service salary cuts, improving conditions for government workers. ?]

@urge_failure_burgerblock  
