The <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> has maintained its discipline and voted down our proposal. Ironically, this defeat has strengthened coalition unity by giving them a common enemy to oppose. However, the working-class base of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">CVP</span>?] watches with growing discontent as their party leadership aligns with capitalist interests.

@improve_relations_burgerblock
title: Improve relations with the Bürgerblock parties.
on-arrival: z_relation += 5*(1-dissent); dvp_relation += 4*(1-dissent); ddp_relation += 4*(1-dissent); lvp_relation += 4*(1-dissent); dnvp_relation += 3*(1-dissent); kvp_relation += 4*(1-dissent); left_dissent += 8; center_dissent += 3; dvp_left += 1; ddp_left += 1; ddp_cohesion -= 0.8; lvp_left += 1; total_burgerblock_dissent -= 0.1; hindenburg_angry_bruning -= 5

We have expanded our diplomatic channels with all parties in the <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> coalition, fostering better cooperation between Social Democracy and the bourgeois center. Our outreach has been particularly successful with the liberal [? if not lvp_formed and dvp_exist: <span style="color: #C0A054;">DVP</span>?][? if lvp_formed: <span style="color: #FFCC00;">LVP</span>?] and <span style="color: #DDAA00;">DDP</span>, and has even helped stabilize the coalition by reducing internal tensions.

However, our leftist comrades view this bourgeois collaboration with deep suspicion, questioning whether we are abandoning our socialist principles.

@exploit_divisions
title: Exploit divisions within the Bürgerblock coalition.
subtitle: Play the liberal and conservative wings against each other.
go-to: exploit_success if total_burgerblock_dissent >= 0.3; exploit_failure if total_burgerblock_dissent < 0.3

@exploit_success
on-arrival: total_burgerblock_dissent += 0.2; dvp_burgerblock_dissent += 0.1; dnvp_burgerblock_dissent += 0.15; kvp_burgerblock_dissent += 0.1; bruning_coalition_loss += 3; left_dissent -= 3; center_dissent += 2; new_middle_spd += 2*(1-dissent); old_middle_spd += 2*(1-dissent); dvp_relation -= 3; dnvp_relation -= 3; kvp_relation -= 3; z_relation -= 2

We have successfully driven wedges between the liberal and conservative wings of the <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span>! By publicly highlighting their contradictions on economic policy and social issues, we have weakened their coalition cohesion. The [? if not kvp_formed and dnvp_ideology == "Moderate": <span style="color: #3E88B3;">DNVP</span>?][? if kvp_formed: <span style="color: #0087DC;">KVP</span>?] conservatives increasingly clash with the [? if not lvp_formed and dvp_exist: <span style="color: #C0A054;">DVP</span>?][? if lvp_formed: <span style="color: #FFCC00;">LVP</span>?] liberals over fundamental questions of economic policy.

Our leftist comrades approve of this more confrontational approach to the bourgeois parties.

@exploit_failure
on-arrival: total_burgerblock_dissent -= 0.1; dvp_relation -= 2; ddp_relation -= 2; lvp_relation -= 2; z_relation -= 2; dnvp_relation -= 2; kvp_relation -= 2; bruning_support += 1

Our attempts to exploit divisions within the <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> have backfired. Instead of creating splits, our obvious maneuvering has actually strengthened their unity against us. The coalition parties have closed ranks, viewing our tactics as proof that Social Democracy cannot be trusted as a constructive partner.

@stay_course

We will continue to provide stable support to the <span style="color: #4A5C2A;">Bürgerblock</span> government, maintaining the delicate balance that keeps both extremes at bay.
